<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1492,1840]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1492,1517]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The cercus of this species (
<figureCitation box="[590,672,1492,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1717,1739]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,198,1690]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1695]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Male caudal appendages, a: lateral view; b: posterior view, c: latero-posterior view. Figures 19 and 21 modified from Rácenis (1960) and Machado (1985) respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230981/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Fig. 
<number box="[643,672,1492,1516]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) is unique within the genus, shorter than S 
<number box="[1159,1188,1492,1516]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" value="10.0">10</number>
and lacking an innerbasal branch; the dorsal branch is slender and directed dorsally, with a small apical hook directed ventrally; the ventral branch is small, rounded, developed as a projection of cercus base. The epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1236,1564,1589]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 21" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1717,1739]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,198,1690]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1695]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 21. Male caudal appendages, a: lateral view; b: posterior view, c: latero-posterior view. Figures 19 and 21 modified from Rácenis (1960) and Machado (1985) respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230981/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Fig. 
<number box="[1208,1236,1564,1588]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
b) is also unique, by its two short and thick branches with apex rounded and joining at base. Genital ligula not described. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
